This reasoning plan provides a general framework for solving mathematical problems, including those presented in the task examples. It involves reading and understanding the problem, identifying relevant concepts and formulas, analyzing and simplifying the problem, developing a solution strategy, implementing the solution strategy, verifying and validating the solution, and communicating the solution. By following this reasoning plan, solvers can arrive at correct answers for a wide range of mathematical problems.
